The antioxidative activity of the three Plectranthus essential oils was investigated by using the β-carotene bleaching test as described by Mothana et al., 2012 [30] with modification. β-carotene solution (1000 μL) which was prepared by dissolving 200 μg in 1 mL chloroform, was added to a flask containing a solution of 200 μL of Tween-20 and 20 μL of linoleic acid. Using rotatory evaporator the chloroform was removed, 100 mL of distilled water was added and the mixture was vigorously shaken for 2 min. 200 μL of the volatile oil (1000 μg/mL) was added to 2 mL of the β-carotene-linoleic acid emulsion and incubated at 40 °C for 2 h. Finally the absorbance was measured at 470 nm at 30 min intervals, by a UV-spectrophotometer (UV mini-1240, Shimadzu, Japan). As a positive control, rutin at a concentration of 1000 μg/mL was utilized. The antioxidative activity was estimated by using the following formula:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
